text.paragraph:
The data described below reflect exposure to VIDAZA in 443 patients with MDS from 4 clinical studies.  Study 1 was a supportive-care controlled trial (subcutaneous administration), Studies 2 and 3 were single arm studies (one with subcutaneous administration and one with intravenous administration), and Study 4 was an international randomized trial (subcutaneous administration) [see Clinical Studies (

                              14.1

                           )].

Elderly patients are more likely to have decreased renal function.  Monitor renal function in these patients [see Dosage and Administration (

                              2.7

                           ) and Warnings and Precautions (

                              5.4

                           )].

Advise females of reproductive potential to use effective contraception during treatment with VIDAZA and for 6 months after the last dose. Advise males with female partners of reproductive potential to use effective contraception during treatment with VIDAZA and for 3 months after the last dose. Advise patients to report known or suspected pregnancy to their physicians immediately [see Warnings and Precautions (

                        5.6

                     ) and Use in Specific Populations (8.3)].
